Create a custom Login Page for Laravel Filament v3 with the following requirements:

## Stack
- Laravel 10+ with Filament v3
- Livewire (built-in Filament)
- Tailwind CSS (Filament default)
- Alpine.js for show/hide password toggle

## Implementation Approach
Extend Filament's default login page — do NOT build from scratch.
Override only what's necessary using Filament's official customization API.

## File Structure
app/
├── Filament/
│   └── Pages/
│       └── Auth/
│           └── CustomLogin.php        # Extended login page
resources/
├── views/
│   └── filament/
│       └── pages/
│           └── auth/
│               └── custom-login.blade.php  # Custom blade (if needed)
app/
└── Providers/
└── Filament/
└── AdminPanelProvider.php     # Register custom login page

## Functional Requirements

### Form Fields
- Email field: type email, label "Email", required
- Password field: type password, label "Password", required, min 8 characters
- Remember Me: checkbox "Ingat Saya", uses Laravel's remember token
- Show/Hide Password: toggle via Alpine.js (x-data, x-bind:type, @click)

### Validation Rules
- Email: required | email format (valid RFC email)
- Password: required | min:8
- Trigger validation on submit
- Show field-level error messages below each input

### Error Handling
- Invalid credentials → show notification or inline error:
  "User dan password tidak ditemukan"
- Use Filament's built-in `$this->throwFailureValidationException()` for consistency

### Redirect
- On success → redirect to Filament panel dashboard (`/admin` or configured panel path)
- If user already authenticated → auto-redirect to dashboard on page load

## Code — Required Patterns

### app/Filament/Pages/Auth/CustomLogin.php
```php
<?php

namespace App\Filament\Pages\Auth;

use Filament\Pages\Auth\Login as BaseLogin;
use Filament\Forms\Components\TextInput;
use Filament\Forms\Components\Checkbox;
use Illuminate\Validation\ValidationException;

class CustomLogin extends BaseLogin
{
    protected function getForms(): array
    {
        return [
            'form' => $this->form(
                $this->makeForm()
                    ->schema([
                        TextInput::make('email')
                            ->label('Email')
                            ->email()
                            ->required()
                            ->autocomplete()
                            ->autofocus(),

                        TextInput::make('password')
                            ->label('Password')
                            ->password()
                            ->revealable()   // Show/hide toggle bawaan Filament v3
                            ->required()
                            ->minLength(8),

                        Checkbox::make('remember')
                            ->label('Ingat Saya'),
                    ])
                    ->statePath('data'),
            ),
        ];
    }

    protected function throwFailureValidationException(): never
    {
        throw ValidationException::withMessages([
            'data.email' => 'User dan password tidak ditemukan.',
        ]);
    }
}
```

### app/Providers/Filament/AdminPanelProvider.php
```php
->login(App\Filament\Pages\Auth\CustomLogin::class)
```

## UI/UX Requirements
- Gunakan Filament default layout (jangan override layout utama)
- Tambahkan logo aplikasi di atas form login (via `$this->getHeading()` atau panel config)
- Responsive by default (Filament sudah handle)
- Gunakan `->revealable()` bawaan Filament untuk show/hide password — JANGAN buat manual kecuali perlu custom icon

## Security Requirements
- Gunakan Laravel's built-in throttle login (sudah ada di Filament)
- Jangan simpan password di session atau log
- Remember Me menggunakan Laravel remember_token di tabel users
- Pastikan kolom `remember_token` ada di tabel users (default migration Laravel)

## Anti-Pattern — Hindari
- Jangan override seluruh login page jika hanya perlu tambah field kecil
- Jangan gunakan custom Blade untuk hal yang bisa di-handle via PHP class
- Jangan bypass `throwFailureValidationException()` — gunakan method ini untuk konsistensi error handling Filament
- Jangan hardcode credential
- Jangan skip `->email()` rule pada field email

## Testing Checklist
- [ ] Email kosong → error "The email field is required"
- [ ] Format email salah → error "The email field must be a valid email address"
- [ ] Password < 8 karakter → error validasi
- [ ] Credential salah → "User dan password tidak ditemukan"
- [ ] Credential benar → redirect ke /admin (atau panel path)
- [ ] Remember Me dicentang → cookie remember aktif
- [ ] Show/hide password toggle berfungsi
- [ ] Sudah login → akses /login auto-redirect ke dashboard